ter by extension + time window.\n- Cursor sources (per your choice):\n  1. `~/Library/Application Support/Cursor/User/workspaceStorage/*/chatSessions/*.json`\n  2. `~/.cursor/projects/*` (scan for `.json` + `.txt`) citeturn0search3\n- Copilot sources:\n  - `~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/*/chatSessions/*.json` citeturn0search0turn0search1\n- Antigravity sources:\n  - `~/Library/Application Support/Antigravity/User/workspaceStorage/*/chatSessions/*.json` (best-effort, based on local layout).\n- Update `src/agents/mod.rs` to expose new high-level functions used by main:\n  - `agents::all_candidate_files(commit_time, window_secs)` gathers candidates from all agent modules.\n  - `agents::all_recent_files(now, since_secs)` gathers recent files for hydrate.\n- Update `src/main.rs` to use these new aggregate functions, replacing per-agent `log_dirs` usage.\n\n### 3) Parse JSON (chatSessions) in metadata + timestamps\n- Update `parse_session_metadata` in `src/scanner.rs`:\n  - Keep JSONL line-by-line parsing.\n  - Add a fallback: if `session_id` or `cwd` is missing, attempt to parse the entire file as JSON.\n  - Extract:\n    - `sessionId` (top-level for chatSessions)\n    - `cwd` from file URIs:\n      - `...baseUri.path`\n      - `...baseUri.fsPath`\n      - `requests[*].variableData.variables[*].value.uri.fsPath`\n    - If a path looks like a file, set `cwd` to its parent directory.\n- Update `session_time_range`:\n  - Support numeric timestamps (milliseconds and seconds).\n  - Include keys `creationDate`, `lastMessageDate`, and `timestamp` in JSON scanning.\n  - If numeric value > 10^12, treat as ms and convert to seconds.\n\n### 4) Candidate file filtering\n- Expand candidate file extensions:\n  - JSONL: `.jsonl` (Claude/Codex)\n  - JSON: `.json` (chatSessions, Cursor projects)\n  - TXT: `.txt` (Cursor projects per referenced layout)\n- Keep time-window filtering to avoid massive scans.\n- For chatSessions directories, only include `.json` files directly under `chatSessions` (non-recursive).\n\n### 5) Cursor labeling rules\n- Enforce your preference:\n  - If the file path indicates Cursor, always label `agent: cursor`.\n  - Do not override Cursor labels based on responder info in JSON.\n\n### 6) Tests\nAdd/extend unit tests:\n- `src/scanner.rs`:\n  - `test_agent_type_display_cursor/copilot/antigravity`\n  - `test_infer_agent_type_cursor/copilot/antigravity_paths`\n  - `test_parse_metadata_chat_session_json` (sessionId, cwd from baseUri/fsPath)\n  - `test_session_time_range_numeric_ms`\n- `src/agents/*`:\n  - Cursor/VS Code chatSessions discovery in temp dirs.\n  - Cursor `~/.cursor/projects` discovery and file extension filtering.\n- `src/note.rs`:\n  - `test_format_cursor_agent`\n  - `test_format_copilot_agent`\n  - `test_format_antigravity_agent`\n\n---\n\n## Test Scenarios\n1. Post-commit hook attaches a note from Cursor chatSessions when commit time matches JSON timestamps.\n2. Hydrate scans Cursor and Copilot chatSessions and attaches notes to matching commits.\n3. Cursor logs always labeled `cursor` even when responder is Copilot.\n4. No false positives when chatSessions directories are empty.\n5. JSONL flow for Claude/Codex unchanged.\n\n---\n\n## Assumptions / Defaults\n- Cursor chat sessions are stored in `~/.cursor/projects/<workspace-id>/` and can include `.json` and `.txt` logs. citeturn0search3\n- VS Code Copilot chat sessions are stored in `.../User/workspaceStorage/<hash>/chatSessions/*.json`. citeturn0search0turn0search1\n- Antigravity uses a VS Code–style `User/workspaceStorage` layout for chat sessions (best-effort based on local layout; no upstream doc found).\n- Cursor logs should always be labeled `cursor` (per your choice), even if Copilot responder metadata exists.\n"}}}
